item.description:
Batch script for running a phython script in each subdirectory
This script runs a python script in each subdirectory of a parent folder. This code is developed to batch process simulation results without any commercial software. A tiny step towards building open source tools.
@echo off set back=%cd% for /d %%i in (%~dp0\*) do ( xcopy &#34;dataExtract.py&#34; &#34;%%i&#34; cd &#34;%%i&#34; echo current directory: cd python3 dataExtract.py ) cd %back% for /d %%i in (%~dp0\*) do ( cd &#34;%%i&#34; del dataExtract.
